<br>
Circled Toe Bones AC6 sta7 cha5 wis5 hps35 mana55 sv.mag5<br>
and...<br>
Shadel Bandit Ring AC 6 hps55 mana55 sv.dis10 svcold5<br>
<br>
the only stats that i deal with are sta/mana/hps/wis thats it. AC and resists are determined differently...<br>
<br>
Circled Toe Bones would score 233<br>
where as Shadel Bandit Ring would score 165... making circled toe bones a lot better ring. <br>
<br>
scoring: the way i determined scoring was to boil it down to its base value.   <br>
2 hps (w/canni4) roughly equal 1 mana...<br>
1 wisdom (200wis+) equals 6 mana...<br>
mana equals mana... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
and stamina roughly equals four hps which equal 2 mana...<br>
<br>
lost ya yet?<br>
based on the formula above i give each stat a value<br>
wis x 12... hps x 1... mana x 2... sta x 4...<br>
<br>
so back to the examples:<br>
Circled Toe Bones has 7sta(7 x 4 = 28 )  + 5wis(5 x 12 = 60) + <br>
35hps(35 x 1 = 35) + 55mana (55 x 2 = 110) added up equals 233<br>
<br>
Shadel Bandit Ring has 55hps (55 x 1 = 55) + 55mana (55 x 2 = 110) added up equals 165<br>
<br>
Now, i realize that circle toe bones is a much better ring and easily determined without the fomula but that was just an quick example to use. i use the formula mostly when i'm deciding to either keep what i got or upgrade for a couple k plat. it helps me to determine if i'm spending my money wisely... <br>
<br>
